SON-RISEA Collaborative Poetry & Literature PlatformSon-Rise is a high-performance web application built on the LAMP stack, dedicated to the digital preservation and showcase of literature. Developed with a focus on clean architecture and sophisticated UI, the platform allows users to explore a vast collection of poems through an interactive, modal-driven interface.  Technical StackBackend: PHP 8.x (Procedural and Functional architecture)  Database: MySQL  Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Custom Variables, Flexbox, and Grid), JavaScript (ES6+)  Assets: Font Awesome 6.5.1  Server Environment: XAMPP / Apache  Key Features1. Dynamic Literature ArchiveThe core of the platform is an interactive grid of poem cards. Each card features:  Smart Truncation: Poem text is automatically clipped using CSS line-clamping to maintain grid symmetry.  Read-More Logic: A sleek centered modal displays the full text and associated imagery without a page reload.  Hover Feedback: Real-time visual cues including red-tinted shadows and a "Read Full Poem" overlay to guide user interaction.  2. Intelligent Search EngineA custom JavaScript-powered search bar allows users to filter the archive instantly.  Multi-Factor Filtering: Searches across Genre, Author, and Title.  UX Fallback: A dedicated "No Results Found" state triggered when search queries return zero matches.  3. Integrated Maintenance SystemThe platform includes a professional-grade maintenance mode managed via a sentinel file.  Trigger: Controlled by the presence of maintenance.enabled in the root directory.  Admin Bypass: Capability to whitelist specific IP addresses for development while the site remains locked for public users.  4. Dynamic Header ArchitectureUsing a centralized head_home.inc.php, the platform programmatically generates page titles based on the current script being executed.  Directory Structureassets/CSS/: Modular stylesheets for the Home, Blog, About, and Poem views.  assets/JS/: Search logic and modal interaction scripts.  components/universal_components/: PHP includes for navigation, headers, and footers.  core_files/: System logic including functions.php, config.php, and session handlers.  pages/HTML/: Source files for the About and Literature views.  Installation and Team WorkflowSetupClone this repository into your local XAMPP/htdocs/ folder.  Ensure your BASE_URL in core_files/config.php matches your local environment.  Import the database schema provided in the SQL folder.Git ProtocolTo avoid merge conflicts when working with the team:Always pull before pushing: git pull origin master --rebase.  Conflict Resolution: If conflicts occur in shared components, use the "Accept Both Changes" feature in VS Code.  Deployment: Only commit stable pages to the master branch.  Maintained by the Son-Rise Development Team